2 RESOLUTION NO. 47 By: Paxton of the Senate
3 and
4 Hilbert of the House
5
6 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
to refer to the people for their approval or
7 rejection a proposed amendment to the Oklahoma
Constitution by adding a new Section 6 to Article
8 III; requiring proof of identity to vote in certain
elections; requiring proof of identity for all
9 authorized methods of voting; requiring Legislature
to enact specific requirements for proof of identity;
10 providing ballot title; ordering special election on
certain date; and directing filing.
11
12
13 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
14 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
15 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
16 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
17 the following proposed amendment to the Oklahoma Constitution by
18 adding a new Section 6 to Article III to read as follows:
19 Section 6. Each voter shall present proof of identity to the
20 appropriate election official when voting at any election authorized
21 by law and conducted by a county election board or the State
22 Election Board. Proof of identity shall be required for any method
23 of voting authorized by law. The Legislature shall enact laws
24
ENGR. S. J. R. NO. 47 Page 1

1 nece ssary to specify the requirements for proof of identity for
2 voting as required by this section.
3 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
4 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
5 the following form:
6 BALLOT TITLE
7 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
8 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
9 This measure adds Section 6 to Article 3 of the Oklahoma
10 Constitution to require proof of identity to vote in any
11 election authorized by law and conducted by a county election
12 board or the State Election Board. The measure requires proof
13 of identity for all authorized methods of voting. The measure
14 requires the Legislature to enact laws to specify requirements
15 for proof of identity for voting.
16 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
17 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
18 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
19 SECTION 3. A special election is hereby ordered to be held
20 throughout the State of Oklahoma on the date of August 25, 2026, at
21 which time the proposed amendment to the Oklahoma Constitution, as
22 set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution, shall be submitted to the
23 people of Oklahoma for their approval or rejection as and in the
24 manner provided by law.
ENGR. S. J. R. NO. 47 Page 2

1 SECTION 4. The President Pro Tempore of the Senate shall,
2 immediately after the passage of this resolution, prepare and file
3 one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in SECTION 2
4 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the Attorney
5 General.
6 Passed the Senate the 26th day of March, 2026.
